-- Ivory Coast Cocoa-Bean Exports Decline 16% to 102,022 Tons in November
-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 2010-12-28T14:27:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/ivory-coast-cocoa-bean-exports-decline-16-to-102-022-tons-in-november.html
Cocoa-bean exports from Ivory Coast,
the world’s largest producer of the chocolate ingredient, fell
16 percent in November from a year earlier, according to data
supplied by the ports of Abidjan and San Pedro.  Shipments dropped to 102,022 metric tons from 121,358 tons
a year earlier, according to the data, which was e-mailed today.
Exports of cocoa products declined to 24,760 tons from 29,246
tons a year earlier, the ports said.  Ivory Coast’s main harvest runs from October through March.  The following is a breakdown of cocoa-bean and cocoa-
